2 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
3 1st Session of the 60th Legislature (2025)
5 and
6 Sacchieri of the Senate
7
8
9 AS INTRODUCED
10 An Act relating to higher education; prohibiting
institutions of higher education from requiring
11 certain purchase as condition for enrollment or
residing on campus; providing for codification;
12 providing an effective date; and declaring an
emergency.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3218.7-2 of Title 70, unless
18 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 Institutions of higher education within The Oklahoma State
20 System of Higher Education shall not require any student to purchase
21 a meal plan as a condition:
22 1. Of enrollment; or
23 2. For residing in on-campus housing.
24 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
